Master Blueprint â€” Summary

1. Nodes & Gradients (Atomic Energies)

N1 â†’ N10: Pure energy/physics states, no personality, each with axes and traits.

Defines push/pull, loose/taut, hot/cold, flux, chaos, etc.

Interaction potential guides sparks, tension, and system dynamics.

2. Archetype Functions (Behavioral Roles)

A1 â†’ A5: Functional labels, linked to nodes.

Describe â€œwhat they do in the system,â€ not who they are.

Drive interaction patterns, conflicts, alliances.

3. Event Skeletons

E1 â†’ E5: Generated from node overlap, pie spin, or triad intersection.

Provides narrative scaffolding, tension arcs, and chaos spikes.

4. Pie Mapping

Pie 1: Hot / Cold / Neutral / Loose / Taut

Pie 2: Push / Pull / Flux / Chaos / Control

Each node and archetype assigned positions for RNG mechanics.

