Gradient / Color Logic for RNG Stat Blocks

Mono â†’ simplest: everything treated equally, just a seed locator, minimal differentiation. Good for quick â€œroll everything same probability.â€

Dual â†’ splits primary function vs secondary modifier. Example: 

Color 1 â†’ node type / archetype trajectory

Color 2 â†’ micro/macro influence or â€œbonus/malusâ€ multiplier

Tri â†’ adds interaction intensity: 

Color 1 â†’ node style (Impulsive/Calculated/etc.)

Color 2 â†’ node action vector (Mischief/Tease/etc.)

Color 3 â†’ triad collision / conflict potential modifier

Penta (5 colors) â†’ full mapping of Pie 1 & Pie 2 axes: 

Hot / Cold / Neutral / Loose / Taut

Push / Pull / Flux / Chaos / Control
â†’ Each axis gets a color, RNG rolls read off color-to-bonus mapping


