How to Use in RNG Engine

Roll triad: 

Pick one Micro node, one Macro node, one Pie spin (or collision triad).

Read colors: 

Color â†’ seed / modifier table.

e.g., Red = +1 Chaos, Teal = +1 Stabilize, Purple = +1 Pull.

Apply bonus: 

Sum Micro + Macro + Pie bonuses â†’ determines RNG personality outcome, micro sparks, or macro arcs.

3D Triad Ball â€“ Color-Coded RNG

Structure

Outer Sphere â€“ Macro Nodes (long-term energy, arcs)

Each Macro node assigned a distinct color (Red-Yellow, Teal, Dark Blue, Bright Green, Gray).

Position in sphere represents Pie 1 (Style Vector) horizontally, Pie 2 (Action Vector) vertically.

Inner Sphere / Core â€“ Micro Nodes (individual sparks)

Micro nodes as smaller orbiting spheres inside the macro shell.

Each Micro node gets its Pie 1 + Pie 2 color mapping (Red, Blue, Green, Orange, Purple).

Orbiting position influenced by triad overlay spin â†’ generates emergent interactions.

Triad Spin / Collision Lines â€“ Interaction vectors

Lines connect micro â†’ macro â†’ triad intersections.

Color blends at collision points to generate dynamic RNG modifiers (e.g., Red + Teal â†’ Orange sparks + stabilization).

Color Gradients

Discrete Mapping: 3 colors for simplicity (Hot = Red, Neutral = Green, Cool = Blue)

Expanded Mapping: 5 colors (Red, Orange, Green, Teal, Blue) for fine-grained RNG bonuses

Gradient Blending: Interpolates between colors for fractional effects.

How it Works

Pick a triad spin (roll RNG spin).

Read macro + micro node positions in 3D sphere.

Intersecting colors â†’ RNG modifiers for personality, sparks, or chaos seeds.

Spin continuously â†’ emergent interactions as nodes orbit and collide.

